The paper proposes a methodology for generating an ordinal utility function from qualitative preference statements, which is a problem commonly encountered in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The methodology is also efficient, which suggests a focus on algorithms and computational complexity, placing it in the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) category. The paper also mentions experiments, which could indicate a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of evaluating the practical effectiveness of the proposed approach.
